      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ اَلرَّجُلُ يُحْرِمُ بِحَجَّةٍ وَ عُمْرَةٍ وَ يُنْشِئُ اَلْعُمْرَةَ أَيَتَمَتَّعُ؟ قَالَ: «نَعَمْ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2549 - Ya'qub ibn Shu'ayb narrated:\nI said to Abu ‘Abdullah (as), \"If a man assumes Ihram for both Hajj and ‘Umrah and begins with the ‘Umrah, does he perform Tamattu‘?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes.\""
        ]
      }
